track.name: Personal Manager
comments: fondly remembering Albert King sharing a bill with Quicksilver Messenger Service...Great night, great show.   Very earsmokin' ly 70's.
Testify,Albert. Genius Legend at work. A shredding of The Blues.
wow ... Albert King is doing the business on this #.  How sweet it is!!

SRV used the exact riff on one his tracks ("may I have a talk with you"), except he sped it up a bit. There's a live versions somewhere where he plays it so much like AK that I thought it was SRV when I heard it here the first time...
Awesome Blues by one of the Greatest of them all
I love this. Blues (R&B) I could listen to all day long.
I love me some awesome blues guitar as well. I could listen all day.
The Velvet Bulldozer... I wanna be your ice cream man when tha day is through... Yeah.
...I remember Makinout to this with one of my first Boyfriends when I introduced him to the Blues....UMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMMM
Love me some good blues guitar. I could listen to this all night.
this is dripping with so much soul my speakers are flooded
